                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "1985152"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "Only one can do it!",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<p><span class=\"font-size-24px\"><strong>Tekst: Warning - Waarschuwing</strong></span><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/userfiles/b/ba20e944793b25eb0cccef13e3a6f7f0b43eb50e.jpg\" class=\"height-149-pixels width-337-pixels\"/></p>\n<p>Machine instructions and warnings are only provided in English. The use of non-English speaking personnel to operate this equipment can cause safety risks, unless the user takes suitable precautions. It is the responsibilty of the employer to ensure that operators understand all instruction/safety mauals and warnings before operating this equipment.</p>\n<p>The following points <strong>must</strong> always be followed:</p>\n<p>Never allow <strong>untrained</strong> personnel to set-up or operate the machine.</p>\n<p>The defeating of any safety device or procedure should never be allowed.</p>\n<p><strong>One (1) person must operate this equipment.</strong> More than one(1)  operator or an assistent will increase the possibility of injury.</p>\n<p>When using the foot switch, the maximum electrode opening should never be more than one (1) inch. This is to prevent the operator from placing any parts of his body within the pinch point area of the machine.</p>\n<p>Read and follow allw warnings and procedures regarding this type of equipment. Faillure to follow these rules will result in the amputation of severe damage to parts of the body</p>\n<p>Beantwoord de volgende vragen:</p>\n<p>1. In hoeveel talen wordt de veiligheidsinstructie geleverd?</p>\n<p>2. Wanneer mag iemand die geen Engels spreekt met de machine werken?</p>\n<p>3. Waarvoor moet de werkgever zorgen als hij niet Engels sprekend personeel met de machine laat werken?</p>\n<p>4. Wie mag er nooit aan de machine komen of werken?</p>\n<p>5. Wanneer mag men een veiligheidsprocedure overslaan?</p>\n<p>6. Waarom mogen er geen twee personen in de buurt komen als de machine in werking is?</p>\n<p>7. Aan welke voorwaarde is men gebonden als men de voetschakelaar gebruikt? Wat is de reden?</p>\n<p>8. Wat kan er volgens de tekst gebeuren als men de vijf veiligheidsregels niet opvolgt/uitvoert?<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/userfiles/b/ba20e944793b25eb0cccef13e3a6f7f0b43eb50e.jpg\" class=\"height-149-pixels width-337-pixels float-right\"/></p>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "1985160"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "Machine operations",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<p><strong><span class=\"underline\">Assignment: machine operations and hazards</span></strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hse.gov.uk/work-equipment-machinery/instructions.htm\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span class=\"underline\">http://www.hse.gov.uk/work-equipment-machinery/instructions.htm</span></strong></a></p>\n<p>Answer the following questions:</p>\n<p>1.       <strong><em>Instructions: What type of information is  mentioned when selling/producing new products?</em></strong></p>\n<p>2.       <strong><em>Information of tests should be provided in some cases. Why is this relevant for environment regulations?</em></strong></p>\n<p>3.       <strong><em>What is meant with 'on-going safety of a product' and were should this be mentioned?</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em>4. <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/userfiles/f/fc1dbd25995d2c66fde64d043c3cb5d84f7fe3ad.jpg\" class=\"height-192-pixels width-256-pixels float-right\"/></em></strong>       <strong><em>Write an interview: think of 5 questions and ask your neighbour. He/she has to do the same!</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em>           Make notes and write the interview Q and A.</em></strong></p>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                }
            ]
        },
